                    <locus from="424a" to="426">Foll. 424a-426</locus>
                    <title ref="" type="supplied">Martyrdom of <persName ref="">Leontius the soldier</persName> <quote xml:lang="syr">ܦ̇ܠܚܐ</quote>), from the place called <quote xml:lang="syr"><placeName>ܐܰܠܕܐ</placeName></quote> (<foreign xml:lang="grc">Ἑλλάς</foreign>?), and of <persName ref="">Publius, or Popillius</persName> (<quote xml:lang="syr"><persName ref="">ܦܘܦܠܝܘܣ</persName></quote>), the monk, in the time of <persName ref="">Diocletian</persName> and <persName ref="">Maximian</persName></title>
                    <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܟ݁ܬܒܝܢܢ ܢ̣ܨܚܢܐ ܕܣܗ̈ܕܐ ܩ̈ܕܝܫܐ. ܠܐܘܢܛܝܘܣ̣ ܘܢܨܝܚܐ ܦܘܦܠܝܘܣ̣ ܨܠܘܬܗܘܢ ܥܡܢ<locus from="424a" to="424a"/></rubric>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="73" xml:id="">
                    <idno type="wright">73</idno>
                    <locus from="426a" to="430">Foll. 426a-430</locus>
                    <title ref="" type="supplied">Martyrdom of <persName ref="">Ṭalyā</persName></title>
                    <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܢܨ̇ܝܚ ܫܘܦܪ̈ܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ ܡܪܝ ܛܠܝܐ. ܨܠܘܬܗ ܥܡܢ.<locus from="426a" to="426a"/></rubric>
                    <note>He was the son of two citizens of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/65">Cyrus</placeName> (<quote xml:lang="syr"><placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/65">ܩܘܪܘܣ</placeName></quote>), named <persName ref="">Sabellius</persName> (<quote xml:lang="syr"><persName ref="">ܣܒܠܝܐ</persName></quote>), and <persName ref="">Sapphira</persName> (<quote xml:lang="syr"><persName ref="">ܫܦܝܪܐ</persName></quote>), and was born about <date>A. Gr. 732</date>, <date>A.D. 421</date><!-- How do I mark up? -->. A voice from heaven announced that at the age of two years he would confute the heathen kings and destroy their idols: <quote xml:lang="syr">ܫܒܪܐ ܕܡܬܝ̣ܠܕ ܠܟܘܢ ܟܕ ܢܗܘܐ ܒܪ ܬܪ̈ܬܝܢ ܫ̈ܢܝܢ܆ ܢ݁ܰܟ̣ܣ ܠܡ̈ܠܟܐ ܥܲܘ̈ܠܐ ܘܢܣ̣ܚܘܦ ܠܦܬܟܪ̈ܝܗܘܢ̣ ܘܢܬܩ̣ܪܐ ܫܡܗ ܛܠܝܐ.<locus facs="426b" to="426b"/></quote> This rumour spreading abroad, the child was brought before <persName ref="">Alexander, the governor of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/52">Byblos or Jubail</placeName></persName> (<quote><placeName ref=" http://syriaca.org/place/52">ܓܷܒܠܷܝܗ̇ ܡܕܝܢܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܣܦ̇ܪ ܝ̇ܰܡ̣ܐ</placeName></quote>), who put both him and his parents to death.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="74" xml:id="">
                    <idno type="wright">74</idno>
                    <locus from="430a" to="438">Foll. 430a-438</locus>
                    <title ref="" type="supplied">Martyrdom of <persName ref="">Probus</persName>, <persName ref="">Tarachus</persName>, and <persName ref="">Andronicus</persName></title>
                    <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܣܗ̈ܕܐ ܢܨ̈ܝܚܐ̣. ܦܪܘܒܘܣ ܘܛܐܪܐܟܘܣ ܘܐܢܕܪܘܢܝܩܘܣ̣ ܨܠܘܬܗܘܢ ܥܡܢ.<locus from="430a" to="430a"/></rubric>
                    <note>See <bibl>the Acta Sanctorum for October., t. v., p. 566.</bibl></note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="75" xml:id="">
                    <idno type="wright">75</idno>
                    <locus from="438a" to="445">Foll. 438a-445</locus>
                    <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/63" type="supplied">Discourse, ascribed to <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/577">Josephus</persName>, on <persName ref="">Eleazar</persName>, <persName ref="">Shamūnī</persName>, and <persName ref="">her seven sons</persName>, generally known as "the fourth book of the Maccabees" </title>
                    <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/63" type="supplied">The Fourth Book of the Maccabees</title>
                    <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܡܐܡܪܐ ܕܝܘܣܝܦܘܣ ܚܟܝܡܐ. ܕܡܟ̣ܬܒ ܠܗ ܥܠ ܐܠܝܥܙܪ݂. ܘܫܡܘܢܝ ܘܒ̈ܢܝܗ̇.<locus from="438a" to="438a"/></rubric>
                    <note>Two portions of the text are missing, viz. ch. x. 1—ch. xii. 11, and ch. xiv. 15—ch. xviii. 11.</note>
                    <note type="errata">Wright's attribution of 4 Maccabees to Josephus represents an ancient Christian tradition which has now been rejected by most scholars on stylistic grounds.</note>
                    <note type="incerta">It is not clear here which version of 4 Maccabees this texts contains.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="76" xml:id="">
                    <idno type="wright">76</idno>
                    <locus from="445a" to="448">Foll. 445a-448</locus>
                    <title ref="" type="supplied">History of <persName ref="">Thecla</persName>, the betrothed of <persName ref="">Thamyris</persName>, and the disciple of <persName ref="">S. Paul</persName></title>
                    <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܬܫܥܝܬܐ ܕܥܠ ܬܩܠܐ܇ ܗ̇ܝ ܕܗ̣ܘܬ ܡܟܝܪܬܗ ܕܬܡܘܪܝܣ ܒܪܗ ܕܡ̇ܠ̣ܟܐ ܘܠܐܚܪܝܬܐ ܬܠܡܝܕܬܗ ܕܦܐܘܠܘܣ ܫܠܝܚܐ<locus from="445a" to="445a"/></rubric>
                    <note>It is imperfect, leaves being missing after foll. 446 and 447.<!-- This should go in the physical description as well. --></note>
                    <note>See <bibl>Tischendorf Acta Apostol. Apocrypha, p. 40;</bibl> <bibl>Surius, Vitae Sanctorum, t. iii., September, p. 263;</bibl> and <bibl>the Acta Sanctorum for Sept., t. vi., p. 546, especially § 3.</bibl></note>
                    <note>This history is wrongly numbered <quote xml:lang="syr">ܥܗ</quote> in the manuscript.</note>
                  </msItem>
